# Storybook stories guardrails

- Scope: `**/_tests/*.stories.ts`.
- **Workspace / config**: Storybook from [`.storybook-workspace/`](../../.storybook-workspace/) (`yarn storybook:run` / `yarn storybook:build`). `staticDirs`, Vite plugins, global preview → `.storybook-workspace/.storybook/` — not root `.storybook/`. **Static output**: `.storybook-workspace/storybook-static/`. **`yarn storybook:build`** + **`yarn test:storybook:smoke`**: **`--quiet --loglevel warn`**; interactive **`yarn storybook:run`** verbose. **Storybook VRT**: `playwright.storybook-visual.config.ts` + `visual-tests/` under `.storybook-workspace/`; root `yarn test:storybook:visual*` → `yarn --cwd .storybook-workspace test:storybook:visual*`. **`storybook.visual.playwright.test.ts`**: **`toHaveScreenshot` `maxDiffPixels`** absorbs small **GitHub Actions** **`windows-latest`** vs local **Windows** raster drift (fonts, subpixel, Chromium) — **pixel difference count** over whole capture, not image width; **README** **Storybook visual baseline policy**, **AGENTS.md** **Storybook VRT pixel budget**. Per-story checks: **`expect.soft`** so one failure does not skip rest; screenshot mismatches attach **Expected / Actual / Diff** on failing **`test.step`** in **`test-results/storybook-visual-report/index.html`**. Verbose VRT progress: **`FA_STORYBOOK_VISUAL_VERBOSE=1`**. **Viewport toolbar** presets + default iframe viewport: **`.storybook-workspace/.storybook/viewportBreakpoints.ts`** (`FANTASIA_STORYBOOK_VIEWPORT_OPTIONS`, **`FANTASIA_STORYBOOK_DEFAULT_VIEWPORT`** from **`preview.ts`**); Playwright visual imports same width/height for desktop baseline — no duplicate breakpoint numbers in stories.
- **Layouts and pages** (`src/layouts/**/_tests/*.stories.ts`, `src/pages/**/_tests/*.stories.ts`): canvas-only (shell/routing). **No** `tags: ['autodocs']`, autogenerated Docs, `parameters.docs.description` / docs prose. Keep `parameters.docs.disable: true` on `meta`. **No** future Storybook docs pages for layouts/pages.
- **`src/components/**` stories**: user-facing behavior + stable contracts (autodocs where already used). **`meta.title`**: **`Components/<bucket>/<ComponentName>`** — **`<bucket>`** under **`src/components/`** (**`dialogs`**, **`floatingWindows`**, **`elements`**, **`foundation`**, **`globals`**, **`projectUI`**, **`other`**); **`<ComponentName>`** = feature folder (leading **`_`** only on three infrastructure helpers per [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) **Helper / wrapper SFC naming (`_` prefix)**). Mirrors filesystem/sidebar. **`foundation/`**: canvas-only catalogues — **`parameters.docs.disable: true`**, **`tags: ['skip-visual']`** for VRT skip; [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) **Foundation components**. **`GlobalLanguageSelector`**: also **`skip-visual`** — Playwright static iframe unreliable for fixed title-bar trigger in screenshots; keep for **`yarn storybook:run`** / Docs/manual review — no VRT baselines. Story mounting nothing under **`#storybook-root`** or **`#root`** after waiter (each checked for element children) + no visible portaled **`q-dialog`**, **`q-menu`**, **`role="dialog"`** → **`tags: ['skip-visual-render-check']`** only with maintainer review; prefer fixing story. Harness-only previews: **`EXCLUDED_STORY_IDS`** in **`.storybook-workspace/visual-tests/storybook.visual.playwright.test.ts`**. **Layouts/pages**: **`Layouts/...`**, **`Pages/...`** titles only. **Modals, `q-dialog`, auto-open on mount**: **`parameters.docs.story.inline: false`** (+ sensible **`iframeHeight`**) on file **`meta`** — Autodocs renders **every** story on one Docs page; **`inline: true`** mounts **all** at once → stacked dialogs/menus “bleed.” Nested Docs iframe loads same preview bundle (Quasar + **`app.scss`**) when preview configured as in repo.
- **No** stories using `A11y/*` naming category.
- Accessibility validation in Vitest/Playwright + manual QA — not Storybook stories.
- **No** stories only validating/forcing `window.faContentBridgeAPIs.extraEnvVariables.TEST_ENV === 'components'`.
- **No** Storybook-only `contentBridgeOverrides.extraEnvVariables.TEST_ENV = 'components'` as story scenario.
- **`TEST_ENV`** branch validation in Playwright/Vitest/component harness — not Storybook docs/stories.
- **i18n**: Preview injects [`.storybook-workspace/.storybook/mocks/externalFileLoader.ts`](../../.storybook-workspace/.storybook/mocks/externalFileLoader.ts) (`defaultMessages`), not `i18n/en-US/index.ts`. New `L_*` wired in `i18n/en-US/index.ts` for Storybook UI → mirror same nested path in `defaultMessages` (import `L_*`, assign `dialogs.newDialog`, etc.) — else stories show raw `$t` key paths while app translates.
